    {
      "id": "doc-4-chunk-1",
      "document_id": "medical-safety-boundary",
      "title": "Medical safety boundary",
      "source": "Medical safety guardrail",
      "url": "local://medical-safety",
      "text": "\u6cbb\u7642, \u85e5\u91cf, \u8655\u65b9, \u91ab\u7642\u5efa\u8b70, \u8001\u4eba\u91ab\u7642, diagnosis, treatment, dose, prescription, medical advice\nContent: For elderly medical questions, provide health education, risk reminders, and guidance about when to contact a clinician or emergency services. Do not provide a definitive diagnosis, prescribe medicine, change medication doses, or replace a clinician. If the user describes emergency warning signs, the response should prioritize contacting local emergency services immediately. In Taiwan, call 119.",
